# Logging (optimized for AI tracing)

Goal: log structured enough that Claude can grep the **full trace** of a request using only the correlation ID.

## Required
- **Structured logs** (JSON), not free-form strings.
- **Correlation/request ID** attached to every log of the same request; generated at the entry point and propagated throughout.
- Each **cross-boundary call** logs both entry and exit with the correlation ID + timing.
- Consistent event-name prefixes: `{{LOG_PREFIX_CONVENTION}}` (e.g. `[auth.login.start]`, `[auth.login.end]`).

## Log levels
- `error`: needs attention. `warn`: abnormal but handled. `info`: business milestones. `debug`: development detail.
- Never log secrets/PII.

## Tooling
- Logging library: {{LOG_LIBRARY}}.
- Where logs go: {{LOG_SINK}}.
